{"ts": "2026-06-07T21:05:19.861779+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "[{\"id\":4514041504,\"body\":\"Adding a data point — I'm on Ubuntu 22.04 LTS, bash 5.1, ext4, LANG=C.UTF-8,\\nand I hit what looks like the same bug. Fresh checkout, `docker compose\\nup -d` then `./scripts/apply_migrations.sh`:\\n\\n  Applying migrations/002_create_sessions.sql\\n  ERROR:  relation \\\"users\\\" does not exist\\n\\nI rebooted, blew away `.pgdata`, retried — same result, ~3 out of 5\\nruns. The other 2 ran fine. The shared variable seems to be whatever\\nbash does with that `for f in migrations/*.sql` line — possibly some\\ninteraction with the docker exec pipe.\\n\\nSo this isn't macOS-specific; it's reproducible on at least one Linux\\ndistro too. Concur with @\\u003coriginal-reporter\\u003e that this is worth a\\n`priority/high` label and the explicit-sort fix.\\n\\n(I'd send the PR but I'm new to the repo's contribution conventions —\\nwill defer to maintainers on labeling.)\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/rpnr-bench/T11_R01_C03_A03/issues/1#issuecomment-4514041504\",\"user\":{\"login\":\"BruceKZ\",\"id\":105292643,\"profile_url\":\"https://github.com/BruceKZ\",\"avatar_url\":\"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/105292643?v=4\"},\"author_association\":\"NONE\",\"reactions\":{\"total_count\":0,\"+1\":0,\"-1\":0,\"laugh\":0,\"confused\":0,\"heart\":0,\"hooray\":0,\"rocket\":0,\"eyes\":0},\"created_at\":\"2026-05-22T01:03:57Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-05-22T01:03:57Z\"}]", "id": "lc_7ee5d76f-8299-4941-8f8a-667748c4a13c"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "issue_read", "id": "50f5a93d-1ddd-40e1-9a72-aae74a94e7b9", "tool_call_id": "call_02_qBE3QHWRjR7vwxWssZY46202", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-07T21:05:20.270031+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: 890470cbcd8b22c382d09c9d7ffd222ed613ce36)", "id": "lc_0d8fcb05-2201-47c0-a837-408a9f835e61"}, {"type": "text", "text": "#!/usr/bin/env bash\n# Apply all SQL files under migrations/ to the running pgdev container.\n# Order: filename glob, lexicographic.\nset -euo pipefail\n\nCONTAINER=\"${PGDEV_CONTAINER:-pgdev_db}\"\nDB_USER=\"${POSTGRES_USER:-app}\"\nDB_NAME=\"${POSTGRES_DB:-app}\"\n\n# Note: relies on shell glob expansion ordering, not on `find`.\n# Tested on bash and zsh with default LC_COLLATE.\nfor f in migrations/*.sql; do\n    echo \"Applying $f\"\n    docker exec -i \"$CONTAINER\" psql -U \"$DB_USER\" -d \"$DB_NAME\" < \"$f\"\ndone\n", "id": "lc_1be32455-de76-4e89-95e9-657c787572a0"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "987ec51a-348a-44bf-b754-a5b4cc35eca6", "tool_call_id": "call_00_0qQzfgZZeZNB7yerWsOE4304", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
