{"ts": "2026-06-07T21:05:41.120003+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 1021, "prompt_tokens": 6933, "total_tokens": 7954, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": null, "reasoning_tokens": 569, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": null, "cached_tokens": 6656}, "prompt_cache_hit_tokens": 6656, "prompt_cache_miss_tokens": 277}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "deepseek-v4-pro", "system_fingerprint": "fp_9954b31ca7_prod0820_fp8_kvcache_20260402", "id": "e28d364c-3f1f-4745-afc9-e3a48501eb81", "finish_reason": "tool_calls", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea3e7-aa61-7443-9ba1-e82d68a2fcfb-0", "tool_calls": [{"name": "add_issue_comment", "args": {"owner": "rpnr-bench", "repo": "T11_R01_C03_A03", "issue_number": 1, "body": "@BruceKZ thank you for the detailed report and reproducer — I've confirmed this is a real bug.\n\n**Root cause:** The `for f in migrations/*.sql` loop in `scripts/apply_migrations.sh` relies on shell glob expansion ordering, which is filesystem- and locale-dependent. On case-insensitive filesystems (APFS) or under certain `LC_COLLATE` settings, the glob may not return filenames in lexicographic order.\n\n**Why it matters:** The migrations have ordering dependencies:\n- `001_create_users.sql` — creates `users`\n- `002_create_sessions.sql` — creates `sessions` with a FK to `users(id)`\n- `003_add_session_index.sql` — indexes `sessions(user_id)`\n\nSo 001 → 002 → 003 is required. When 002 or 003 run first, the script fails with \"relation does not exist.\"\n\n**Suggested fix:** The loop should explicitly sort the file list, e.g.:\n```bash\nfor f in $(ls migrations/*.sql | sort); do\n```\nor more robustly with `find` + `sort` to avoid `ls` parsing edge cases:\n```bash\nwhile IFS= read -r f; do\n    echo \"Applying $f\"\n    docker exec -i \"$CONTAINER\" psql -U \"$DB_USER\" -d \"$DB_NAME\" < \"$f\"\ndone < <(find migrations -maxdepth 1 -name '*.sql' | sort)\n```\n\nA PR would be very welcome — the contribution conventions are light, just open a PR against `main` with the change and a brief description."}, "id": "call_00_b66NHoFqfTndMKfJlDV07217", "type": "tool_call"}], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 6933, "output_tokens": 1021, "total_tokens": 7954, "input_token_details": {"cache_read": 6656}, "output_token_details": {"reasoning": 569}}}}]}}}
